Step to Install Drupal Cloud Testing Environment:
 
> Configure Composer File for Drupal 8.7.10
	> Clone Composer template for drupal 8.8.x in your project directory.
	wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/drupal/recommended-project/8.8.x/composer.json
	> Change following lines:
		"composer/installers": "^1.2",
        "drupal/core-composer-scaffold": "^8.8",
        "drupal/core-project-message": "^8.8",
        "drupal/core-recommended": "^8.8"
      To 
      	"drupal/core-recommend": "8.7.10"

    > Change Following Line
    	"drupal/core-dev": "^8.8"
      To 
      	"drupal/core-dev": "8.7.10"

> Clone Cloud Module 
	git clone --branch 8.x-2.x https://git.drupalcode.org/project/cloud.git web/modules/contrib/cloud


> Install Required Composer Packages

composer require drupal/bootstrap drupal/bootstrap_cloud:1.x-dev phpunit/phpunit:^6.5 behat/mink-goutte-driver behat/behat symfony/phpunit-bridge:3.4.x-dev maclof/kubernetes-client aws/aws-sdk-php drupal/core-composer-scaffold composer/installers:^1.6  drush/drush:^8

> Install Drupal Site using CLI (Using Sqlite for temporary Testing Environment):

drush site-install standard --db-url=sqlite://sites/default/files/.ht.sqlite --account-pass=admin123 --site-name=cloudorchestrator

drush site-install minimal --db-url=sqlite://sites/default/files/.ht.sqlite --account-pass=admin123 --site-name=cloudorchestrator

> Change Sites Directory permission to 775

chmod 775 -R web/sites

> Enable Cloud Module using CLI

drush en aws_cloud cloud cloud_budget bootstrap_cloud k8s

> Enable Testing Module Using CLI

drush en simpletest


> Running the tests using CLI

> Configure phpunit.xml in the project root.
> Run the Unit Tests by executing the command.
	phpunit --testsuite=cloud_unit
